# Cursor Rules for Snorkel Backend

## Code Style Guidelines

- Follow PEP 8 with a 120-character line limit
- Use double quotes for strings consistently
- Use type hints where appropriate
- Follow the existing import structure and patterns
- Use f-strings for string formatting
- Prefer list comprehensions over map/filter when readable
- Use meaningful variable names (avoid single letters except for loops)

## Project-Specific Rules

- Use SQLAlchemy for database operations
- Follow Flask application patterns established in the codebase
- Use the existing error handling patterns
- Follow the established route naming conventions
- Use the existing model patterns for database models
- Prefer explicit imports over wildcard imports

## File Organization

- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Use descriptive function and variable names
- Add docstrings for public functions and classes
- Follow the existing module structure

## Database Patterns

- Use the existing db session patterns
- Follow the established model relationships
- Use proper transaction handling with commit/rollback
- Follow the existing query patterns

## Error Handling

- Use try/except blocks appropriately
- Log errors with meaningful messages
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes
- Follow the existing error response patterns
